// Get input data
const data = $node["clientdata"].json;

const tz = data.Time_Zone  // Example input, you can change it

// Mapping offsets to common abbreviations
const offsetToTZ = {
  "-12:00": "AoE",      // Anywhere on Earth
  "-11:00": "NUT",      // Niue Time
  "-10:00": "HST",      // Hawaii Standard Time
  "-09:00": "AKST",     // Alaska Standard Time
  "-08:00": "PST",      // Pacific Standard Time
  "-07:00": "MST",      // Mountain Standard Time
  "-06:00": "CST",      // Central Standard Time
  "-05:00": "EST",      // Eastern Standard Time
  "-04:00": "AST/EDT",  // Atlantic Standard / Eastern Daylight
  "-03:00": "ART",      // Argentina Time
  "-02:00": "GST",      // South Georgia Time
  "-01:00": "AZOT",     // Azores Time
  "+00:00": "UTC",      // Coordinated Universal Time
  "+01:00": "CET",      // Central European Time
  "+02:00": "EET",      // Eastern European Time
  "+03:00": "MSK",      // Moscow Standard Time
  "+04:00": "GST",      // Gulf Standard Time
  "+05:00": "PKT",      // Pakistan Standard Time
  "+05:30": "IST",      // India Standard Time
  "+06:00": "BST",      // Bangladesh Standard Time
  "+07:00": "ICT",      // Indochina Time
  "+08:00": "CST/SGT",  // China Standard / Singapore Time
  "+09:00": "JST",      // Japan Standard Time
  "+09:30": "ACST",     // Australian Central Standard Time
  "+10:00": "AEST",     // Australian Eastern Standard Time
  "+11:00": "SBT",      // Solomon Islands Time
  "+12:00": "NZST",     // New Zealand Standard Time
};

// Get abbreviation or fallback
const abbreviation = offsetToTZ[tz] || "Unknown Timezone";

return [{ offset: tz, abbreviation }];
